quran[15]{c,v,t,f}:
  37,85,"[And] when he said to his father and his people, "
  37,86,"Is it falsehood [as] gods other than Allāh you desire?"
  37,87,"Then what is your thought about the Lord of the worlds?"
  38,64,"Indeed, that is truth [i.e., reality] - the quarreling of the people of the Fire."
  38,65,"Say, [O Muḥammad], ",footnotes:1:Refer to footnotes in 12:39.
  38,66,"Lord of the heavens and the earth and whatever is between them, the Exalted in Might,{1} the Perpetual Forgiver.",footnotes:1:Honored for absolute power associated with wisdom and justice.,footnotes:2:Who continually conceals sins and faults.
  39,49,"And when adversity touches man, he calls upon Us; then when We bestow on him a favor from Us, he says, "
  39,50,"Those before them had already said it, but they were not availed by what they used to earn."
  39,51,"And the evil consequences of what they earned struck them. And those who have wronged of these [people] will be struck [i.e., afflicted] by the evil consequences of what they earned; and they will not cause failure.{1}",footnotes:1:i.e., prevent Allāh from what He wills or escape from the punishment.
  40,28,"And a believing man from the family of Pharaoh who concealed his faith said, "
  40,29,"O my people, sovereignty is yours today, [your being] dominant in the land. But who would protect us from the punishment of Allāh if it came to us?"
  40,30,"And he who believed said, ",footnotes:1:i.e., the days on which Allāh sent His punishment upon those who rejected their prophets in former times.
  41,7,"Those who do not give zakāh, and in the Hereafter they are disbelievers."
  41,8,"Indeed, those who believe and do righteous deeds - for them is a reward uninterrupted."
  41,9,"Say, "